        "type": "scenario",
        "question": "Ken is a freelance photographer. He can buy Equipment Policy A (annual premium NT$18,000, deductible NT$5,000 per claim) or retain all equipment risk. His lens kit is worth NT$120,000. Historical data (his own + peers) suggests a 4% annual chance of theft total loss of the kit. (1) Compute the expected loss if he retains risk. (2) Give a decision rule comparing premium to expected loss (before loading discussion). (3) Name one non-insurance risk control for theft. / 肯恩為自由攝影師，可投保器材險 A：年保費 18,000 元、每次事故自負額 5,000 元；或完全自留。鏡頭組價值 120,000 元，估計每年遭竊全損機率 4%。(1) 自留時期望損失？(2) 以保費與期望損失初步比較之決策規則？(3) 舉一項竊盜之非保險風險控制。",
